# Instinct RPG — Primer typography tiers

Three tiers — **do not mix without Annie explicitly asking.**

| Tier | Font | Use for |
|------|------|---------|
| **1 — Chrome** | `Cinzel` | Hero, section eyebrows, section titles, callout labels, step column names (`Build` / `Roll` / `Read`), card-type chips, footer labels |
| **2 — Narrative body** | `Crimson Pro` (inherits from `body`) | Section paragraphs, step bodies, walkthrough text, glossary/FAQ answers, card-type descriptions, chargen descriptions, callout body, golden-rule quotes |
| **3 — Sub-labels** | `system-ui` stack | `.step-sub-title`, `.ex-step-num`, `.chargen-label` only |

## Hard rules

1. **Never** move tier-2 detail paragraphs to sans-serif unless Annie explicitly requests it (June 2026
   playtest reverted a sans-body experiment).
2. **Card-mounted text** uses Card Studio typography inside `.cardwrap` (`system-ui` / EB Garamond per
   card template) — separate from primer page tiers.
3. Dice numeric labels (`.die`, `.die-label`) may stay as defined in the primer stylesheet; don’t
   extend sans into prose blocks.
4. New sub-topic headings in the primer → tier **3**, not tier 1, unless they are true section titles.

## Adding new UI text

- New **section** → tier 1 for title, tier 2 for body.  
- New **in-step label** (Aid, Misses, Step 2) → tier 3.  
- New **FAQ/glossary** content → tier 2.

